13: Why! Why did you betray us?!
28: All you know how to do... is kill...
37: I can't believe I fell asleep here...
40:
It's been a long time since I last saw
that dream.
50: Hold on. What are you doing?!
53:
Why, my little cupcake. Something
for your sake, of course.
56: You're just doing whatever you want!
65:
I must speak with you. Come with
me.
68:
No, thank you. I'd rather not get
skewered again and die today.
73:
Sheesh, even for a joke, that's pretty
dark.
87:
Uh... Well, whatever that is, I hope it
goes well...
93:
Not the first time you've called for a
private rendezvous, is it?
96:
What was it you asked me the last
time? Ah, yes. "What are you
scheming?"
100:
You once told me that you found it
good that the world was changing.
102:
The role of the Champions, the
Goddess, the Overlords... You knew
about everything, didn't you?
105:
How astute. Yes, from the start...
everything I did, I did armed with
that knowledge.
108: Do you still hate me despite it?
112:
I must admit that I do... But I know
that I would've lost everything,
regardless of your meddling.
115:
Now, in this ever-changing world, I
must continue to choose my own
path, but at least I won't be
traversing it alone.
123:
However, there is one thing I don't
understand.
127:
Why do you continue to play your
games?
134:
You're probably the oldest adult
among us, and yet you refuse to act
like one.
136:
In fact, you really could've been
nicer to me when we first met. I was
hardly a teen—
146:
Hehehe, it's not polite to bring up a
lady's age.
149:
Y-you should really learn to show
some restraint before you push
everyone around you away!
153:
I... I would never be abandoned so
easily.
157:
Alk has quite the emotional side. If
you prod him too much, he might
actually cut things off once and for
all!
166:
And what guarantee do you have of
that? Don't say I didn't warn you!
174: Is that all you wanted to say?
176:
I haven't revealed all the knowledge
at my disposal—much of it you know
nothing of.
183:
Stella is the type of girl who would
notice someone crying, even if
nobody else did.
185:
As long as she remains by your side,
I have nothing to fear.
192: Light. Belsidia. What are you doing?
196:
Just having a talk. It was...
enlightening on many fronts.
201:
Belsidia, what was Light so happy
about—
206:
Oh, Stella, my pumpkin! You would
never come to hate me, would you?
222:
Oh, but you don't like it when I
embrace you...
226: Unfortunately, I do need to breathe.
230:
But if you do it from behind, I should
be fine.
243:
Oh, cupcake... Perhaps if I do it like
this to Alk, he'll allow it as well...
